<p><placeName>Brazoria </placeName><date when="1834-02-22">Feby 22d 1834</date></p>
<p><persName>James F Perry Esq,</persName></p>

<p>Your Esteemed favour under <date when="1834-02-21">yesterdays date</date> has been received
and I have delivered <persName>Simon </persName>Six Hoes of his own choice. We have no
information of <persName>Col. Austin</persName> since you was here</p>

<p>I have heard that <persName>McQueen </persName>has gone into the <placeName>interior </placeName>to hear
[what] was become of him but of this I am not certain <persName>Mr Williams</persName>
Expected now here and we may here something then</p>

<p>I have charged the hoes to you with the understanding you are to
pay by crediting <persName>Capt H Austin</persName> with them</p>

<p>I have not heard anything from <persName>Dick </persName>yet. Nor have I found any
one that is willing to work. I am in hope to make a sale for <persName>Capt
H Austin</persName> to help him out. You I suppose have heard of <persName>Hunter
Smiths overseer</persName> being drowned at <placeName>Bolivar </placeName>it happend when <persName>Capt
H. A</persName> was with me&#8212;</p>

<p><persName>Edmund Andrews</persName></p>

<p>[Addressed:] <persName>James F Perry Esq</persName>   <placeName>Peach Point </placeName>  pr <persName>Simon</persName></p>



        </div1>
